ce:section.ce:para:
As the AIS QDs were lyophilized for obtaining the respective powder, allowing storage for longer periods of time, the optical properties of QDs before and after the lyophilization process were assessed to observe any possible modification in the emission spectra and/or QY. In Fig. 1
                         are shown the normalized PL spectra of all nanomaterials and in the case of the semiconductors QDs the comparison between their emission bands before and after the lyophilization. No significant variation on the emission bands and on the maximum emission wavelengths was verified for the TMA-AIS and D-Pen-AIS QDs (Table 1
                        ). Considering the MPA-AIS QDs, as a size-selective precipitation was carried out before the lyophilization, the emission band narrowed and the maximum emission wavelength had a bathochromic deviation (from 598 to 610 nm).
